The course introduces different directions in gender studies (feminism, masculinity and queer studies) and central problems related to gender in the humanities. It introduces central terms (gender, difference, subjectivity, body, sexuality) and theories (feminist theories, masculinity theories, queer theory) of gender studies and shows their potential of application in different areas. The course helps to develop basic skills in identifying and using gender as an analytical category in the learning process.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to open the role and patterns of gender in different cultural phenomena and processes and to give a survey of different treatments of gender and gendered approaches in the humanities.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students will gain an understanding of the manifestations of gender in different cultures and historical periods as well as the ability to use gender as an analytical category for answering different research questions. Students will improve their skills of critical thinking and analysis.
